        "timeoriginalestimate": null,
        "description": "Dask seems to be selectively do compression if it is found to be useful. They sort of pick 10kb of sample upfront to calculate compression and if the results are good then the whole batch is compressed. This seems to save de-compression effort on receiver side.\r\n\u00a0\r\nPlease take a look at\u00a0[https://blog.dask.org/2016/04/14/dask-distributed-optimizing-protocol#problem-3-unwanted-compression]\r\n\u00a0\r\nThought\u00a0this could be relevant to arrow batch transfers as well.\u00a0",
